%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4/batch-gateway.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proc as Batch Processor
    participant GW as Inference Gateway<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over Client,GW: Flow 1: File Upload
    Client->>API: POST /v1/files (multipart/form-data)<br/>X-MaaS-User: tenant-id<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
    API->>S3: Upload file<br/>TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>API: Upload confirmation
    API->>Redis: Store file metadata<br/>TLS (optional), Password
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API-->>Client: 200 File object (JSON)

    Note over Client,GW: Flow 2: Batch Job Creation
    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches<br/>X-MaaS-User: tenant-id<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
    API->>Redis: Store batch metadata<br/>TLS (optional), Password
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue<br/>TLS (optional), Password
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API-->>Client: 200 Batch object (JSON)

    Note over Client,GW: Flow 3: Batch Job Processing
    loop Poll for pending jobs
        Proc->>Redis: Dequeue from priority queue<br/>TLS (optional), Password
        Redis-->>Proc: BatchJobPriority
    end
    Proc->>Redis: Get job metadata<br/>TLS (optional), Password
    Redis-->>Proc: Batch job details

    loop For each request in JSONL file
        Proc->>GW: POST inference request<br/>TLS 1.2+ (mTLS optional)<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
        GW-->>Proc: Inference response
    end

    Proc->>Redis: Update job status<br/>TLS (optional), Password
    Redis-->>Proc: OK

    Note over Client,GW: Flow 4: Batch Job Cancellation
    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{batch_id}/cancel<br/>X-MaaS-User: tenant-id
    API->>Redis: Remove from priority queue
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API->>Redis: Publish cancel event<br/>(event channel)
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API->>Redis: Update status to cancelled
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API-->>Client: 200 Cancelled batch object
